b-family-blames-polic/?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>In a Punjab village, family of rape victim who committed suicide blame police.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/2724e70b/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884205455/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/2724e70b/a2.htm"&gt;&lt;img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884205455/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/2724e70b/a2.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151884205455/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/2724e70b/a2t.img" border="0"/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">India</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Sex Crimes</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Police</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Women's Rights</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 07:34:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://india.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/after-rape-victim-commits-suicide-in-punjab-family-blames-polic/</guid><dc:creator>By NIHARIKA MANDHANA</dc:creator></item><item><title>Letter from India: City Setting, but Village Mentalities</title><link>http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/asia/03iht-letter03.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>The protest movement that has sprung up in Delhi after a brutal rape in December is largely a lament of the city against a nation that has blamed attacks on women on the women's own modernity.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/271e7d2f/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884174775/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/271e7d2f/a2.htm"&gt;&lt;img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884174775/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/271e7d2f/a2.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151884174775/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/271e7d2f/a2t.img" border="0"/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">India</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">New Delhi (India)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Sex Crimes</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Women and Girls</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Police Brutality and Misconduct</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Politics and Government</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Social Conditions and Trends</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Sexual Harassment</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Urban Areas</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Women's Rights</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 07:30:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/asia/03iht-letter03.html</guid><dc:creator>By MANU JOSEPH</dc:creator></item><item><title>IHT Special: Syrian Refugees Strain Resources in Jordan</title><link>http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/middleeast/syrian-refugees-strain-resources-in-jordan.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>Despite plans by aid organizations to help at least 50,000 urban refugees, a large number will be left out because of the rising numbers of Syrians fleeing across the border each day.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/2722983e/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Middle East and North Africa Unrest (2010- )</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Refugees and Displaced Persons</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Syria</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Jordan</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 07:30:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/middleeast/syrian-refugees-strain-resources-in-jordan.html</guid><dc:creator>By RANA F. SWEIS</dc:creator></item><item><title>Spain’s Chinese Immigrants Thrive in Tough Economy</title><link>http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/europe/spains-chinese-immigrants-thrive-in-tough-economy.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>Chinese immigrants to Spain have managed not only to survive the economic crisis; they are thriving, buying distressed properties and starting businesses.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/2722983b/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883981963/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/2722983b/a2.htm"&gt;&lt;img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883981963/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/2722983b/a2.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151883981963/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/2722983b/a2t.img" border="0"/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/nyt_org_all">Lenovo Group|LNVGY|NQB</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Spain</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org_all">European Union</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">China</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Immigration and Emigration</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">European Sovereign Debt Crisis (2010- )</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 07:30:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/europe/spains-chinese-immigrants-thrive-in-tough-economy.html</guid><dc:creator>By DAN BILEFSKY</dc:creator><media:credit scheme="urn:ebu">Samuel Aranda for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Jiajia Wang, 24, in Barcelona. She works four jobs and sends her parents 1,000 euros a month. They arrived in the 1990s speaking no Spanish, and worked 12-hour days in a restaurant.</media:description><media:content height="75" lang="" width="75" url="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2013/01/03/world/europe/03iht-barcelona/03iht-barcelona-thumbStandard.jpg" /></item><item><title>France's Less Joyous New Year's Tradition</title><link>http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/europe/frances-less-joyous-new-years-tradition.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>The government resumed its yearly announcement of the number of holiday car burnings.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/27229838/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883981965/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/27229838/a2.htm"&gt;&lt;img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883981965/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/27229838/a2.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151883981965/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/27229838/a2t.img" border="0"/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Crime and Criminals</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Politics and Government</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Arson</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Insurance</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">France</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">New Year</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 07:30:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/europe/frances-less-joyous-new-years-tradition.html</guid><dc:creator>By DAVID JOLLY</dc:creator></item><item><atom:link href="http://rendezvous.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/01/02/indian-women-need-a-political-party/?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" rel="standout" /><title>IHT Rendezvous: Indian Women Need a Political Party</title><link>http://rendezvous.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/01/02/indian-women-need-a-political-party/?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>Only a political party whose fate is tied to how women perceive it can begin to influence the system in a deep way.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/271e70e2/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883967350/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/271e70e2/a2.htm"&gt;&lt;img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883967350/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/271e70e2/a2.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151883967350/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/271e70e2/a2t.img" border="0"/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">India</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Legislatures and Parliaments</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Sex Crimes</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Women and Girls</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Page Two</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 07:21:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://rendezvous.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/01/02/indian-women-need-a-political-party/</guid><dc:creator>By MANU JOSEPH</dc:creator><media:credit scheme="urn:ebu">Raveendran/Agence France-Presse — Getty Images</media:credit><media:description>A protest in New Delhi on Tuesday.</media:description><media:content height="75" lang="" width="75" url="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2013/01/03/blogs/03ihtrdv-letter/03ihtrdv-letter-thumbStandard.jpg" /></item><item><atom:link href="http://re