ys-weakness/</guid><dc:creator>By DIDI KIRSTEN TATLOW</dc:creator></item><item><atom:link href="http://india.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/indian-women-celebrate-dented-and-painted-moniker/?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" rel="standout" /><title>India Ink: Indian Women Celebrate 'Dented and Painted' Moniker</title><link>http://india.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/indian-women-celebrate-dented-and-painted-moniker/?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>A remark by the President's son about women in their (gasp) thirties, refuses to go away.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/2724bbbe/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Mukherjee, Pranab</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Demonstrations, Protests, and Riots</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Sex Crimes</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Women and Girls</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">Social Networking (Internet)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/">New Year</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 07:12:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://india.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/indian-women-celebrate-dented-and-painted-moniker/</guid><dc:creator>By MALAVIKA VYAWAHARE and SARITHA RAI</dc:creator></item><item><atom:link href="http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/middleeast/pakistani-girl-shot-by-taliban-will-stay-in-britain.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" rel="standout" /><title>World Briefing | Europe: Pakistani Girl Shot by Taliban Will Stay in Britain</title><link>http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/middleeast/pakistani-girl-shot-by-taliban-will-stay-in-britain.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>The father of a teenage Pakistani activist shot in the head by the Taliban for advocating girls’ education has been given a diplomatic post in Britain.&lt;img width='1' heig