mes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Damascus (Syria)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_per">Pillay, Navi</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Syria</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 06:48:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/middleeast/syria-damascus-developments.html</guid><dc:creator>By ANNE BARNARD</dc:creator><media:credit scheme="urn:ebu">Muhammad Najdet Qadour/Shaam News Network, via Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Smoke rose Wednesday over Binnish, in Idlib Province, in a photo released by activists. The United Nations released a report that said more than 60,000 people had died in Syria’s conflict.</media:description><media:content height="75" lang="" width="75" url="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2013/01/03/world/syria/syria-thumbStandard.jpg" /></item><item><atom:link href="http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/asia/deadly-car-crash-time-to-play-the-thai-lottery.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" rel="standout" /><title>Deadly Car Crash? Time to Play the Thai Lottery</title><link>http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/asia/deadly-car-crash-time-to-play-the-thai-lottery.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>Thais, who often mix superstition with a proclivity for fun, play the underground lottery with numbers gleaned from calamity, believing that disaster can beget good fortune.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/2723290c/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883985987/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/2723290c/a2.htm"&gt;&lt;img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883985987/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/2723290c/a2.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151883985987/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/2723290c/a2t.img" border="0"/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Thailand</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Economic Conditions and Trends</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Lotteries</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/mdes">Superstitions</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Numbers</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_org_all">Chulalongkorn University</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 06:48:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/asia/deadly-car-crash-time-to-play-the-thai-lottery.html</guid><dc:creator>By THOMAS FULLER</dc:creator><media:credit scheme="urn:ebu">Giulio Di Sturco for the International Herald Tribune</media:credit><media:description>Paan Padthong, a fortune teller at the Mae Nak shrine, where Thais go for inspiration in picking lottery numbers.</media:description><media:content height="75" lang="" width="75" url="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2013/01/03/world/thailand1/thailand1-thumbStandard.jpg" /></item><item><atom:link href="http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/africa/central-africa-on-the-brink-rebels-halt-their-advance.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" rel="standout" /><title>Central Africa on the Brink, Rebels Halt Their Advance</title><link>http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/africa/central-africa-on-the-brink-rebels-halt-their-advance.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>A new willingness to talk raises hope of a peaceful resolution to a conflict that has driven thousands of civilians from their homes in search of refuge.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/272340da/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884197690/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/272340da/a2.htm"&gt;&lt;img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151884197690/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/272340da/a2.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151884197690/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/272340da/a2t.img" border="0"/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Defense and Military Forces</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Central African Republic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/des">Demonstrations, Protests, and Riots</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_per">Bozize, Francois</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 06:48:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/africa/central-africa-on-the-brink-rebels-halt-their-advance.html</guid><dc:creator>By SCOTT SAYARE</dc:creator><media:credit scheme="urn:ebu">Ben Curtis/Associated Press</media:credit><media:description>A convoy of soldiers from Chad who are fighting in support of President Francois Bozize of the Central African Republic, traveled on the road to Damara, north of the capital, Bangui, on Wednesday.</media:description><media:content height="151" lang="" width="151" url="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2013/01/03/world/03african_337/03african_337-moth.jpg" /></item><item><atom:link href="http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/europe/putin-orders-new-system-for-russian-parliamentary-elections.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" rel="standout" /><title>Putin Orders New System for Russian Parliamentary Elections</title><link>http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/europe/putin-orders-new-system-for-russian-parliamentary-elections.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>The move by President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia to establish a mixed electoral system would alter the way seats are filled in the State Duma, the lower house of Parliament, and could help solidify his power.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/27218423/mf.gif' borde