=rss&amp;emc=rss" rel="standout" /><title>Philippines May Curb Pursuit of Marcos’s Wealth</title><link>http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/asia/philippines-may-end-pursuit-of-marcos-wealth.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><description>With the family of the former dictator Ferdinand Marcos politically ascendant, efforts to pursue assets connected to his leadership days have faltered.&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='http://rss.nytimes.com/c/34625/f/642565/s/271e685d/mf.gif' border='0'/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883964696/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/271e685d/a2.htm"&gt;&lt;img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/151883964696/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/271e685d/a2.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/151883964696/u/0/f/642565/c/34625/s/271e685d/a2t.img" border="0"/&gt;</description><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_per">Marcos, Ferdinand Jr</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Philippines</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_per">Marcos, Imelda R</category><pubDate>Thu, 03 Jan 2013 06:48:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/asia/philippines-may-end-pursuit-of-marcos-wealth.html</guid><dc:creator>By FLOYD WHALEY</dc:creator><media:credit scheme="urn:ebu">Alberto Marquez/Associated Press</media:credit><media:description>President Ferdinand E. Marcos with his wife, Imelda, in Manila on Feb. 25, 1986, hours before they fled the Philippines.</media:description><media:content height="151" lang="" width="151" url="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2013/01/03/world/philippines/philippines-moth.jpg" /></item><item><atom:link href="http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/03/world/middleeast/report-says-mubarak-dictated-fierce-response-to-egypt-protests.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" rel="standout" /><title>Mubarak Dictated Response to Protest